      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver with documented version control and release testing. Internal post-processing scripts under version control with peer review.",
      "rationale": "The RANS solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022R1) is a commercially validated code with documented QA processes. The hemolysis damage integral post-processing module is maintained under Git version control with peer review of commits. No independent audit of the multi-threaded post-processing module for race conditions or numerical edge cases was conducted; solver robustness was assessed informally by the team with no systematic fault-mode enumeration or quantitative stability metrics recorded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy verification for primary transport equations using manufactured solutions or benchmark cases consistent with MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Fluent solver order-of-accuracy documented in vendor verification reports for incompressible RANS equations. Hemolysis power-law integration verified against published analytic test cases for simple Couette flow. All verification runs completed nominally with residuals converging to 1e-5. No testing of numerical behavior at degenerate mesh elements or extreme shear rate boundary conditions was performed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% for hemolysis index QoI at selected operating points.",
      "rationale": "GCI computed at two operating points (OP1 and OP2) using Richardson extrapolation across three mesh levels. GCI for hemolysis index: 3.2% (OP1), 4.1% (OP2), both within the 5% acceptance threshold. Medium mesh (5.8M cells) selected for production runs. GCI not evaluated at extreme off-design conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) documented and matched within measurement uncertainty to CFD inputs.",
      "rationale": "FDA bench test conditions documented with traceability to ASTM F1841. Inlet flow rates controlled to ±0.05 L/min; rotational speed to ±10 RPM. Blood analogue fluid viscosity and density matched to CFD inputs within 2%. Test temperature maintained at 37±0.5°C."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted RH index within 25% of experimental RH across all 5 operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "CFD RH predictions compared against experimental measurements at all 5 operating conditions. Maximum deviation 18%, mean deviation 11%. Acceptance criterion of 25% satisfied at all conditions. Comparison performed on nominal solver outputs; no assessment of output sensitivity to potential numerical perturbations or near-singular flow conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) directly maps to clinical hemolysis risk metric used in predicate device comparison.",
      "rationale": "RH index derived from power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) is the accepted QoI for CFD hemolysis studies per FDA guidance. Direct correspondence between computational RH and bench-measured normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) established through published correlation. QoI selection justified for MRL 2 decision context."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments use the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under CPB-representative flow conditions spanning the intended operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is the reference geometry for the COU. Operating conditions span the clinical CPB envelope (2–5 L/min, 1500–3000 RPM). Validation activities directly relevant to the COU decision. Predicate device comparison performed under matched conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated by residual reduction to 1e-5 and stabilization of hemolysis QoI monitor to within 0.5% over final 200 iterations.",
      "rationale": "All production runs achieved continuity residuals below 1e-5 and velocity residuals below 1e-6. Hemolysis QoI monitor stabilized to within 0.3% over final 200 iterations in all cases. Solver completed nominally for all 5 operating conditions. Convergence behavior at intermediate iterations not systematically analyzed; no testing performed for conditions that might trigger iterative divergence or floating-point overflow in the damage integral accumulation loop."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by a second analyst for boundary condition assignment and material property inputs.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup performed by senior analyst. Boundary condition assignments, turbulence model selection (k-omega SST), and material property inputs verified against documented test conditions. No discrepancies identified. MRL 2 requires only basic use error controls."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model selection justified by published literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST turbulence model selected based on published performance for rotating machinery internal flows. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al., exponents alpha=0.785, beta=2.416) consistent with FDA-referenced literature. Sensitivity of RH to hemolysis model coefficients assessed via ±10% parameter perturbation; RH varied by less than 8%. Model form uncertainty considered acceptable for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty in key model inputs (viscosity, density, inlet velocity profile) propagated to QoI uncertainty estimate.",
      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed for fluid viscosity (±5%), density (±1%), and inlet velocity profile (uniform vs. developed). Combined input uncertainty contribution to RH estimated at ±6%. Geometric tolerances of pump components incorporated as nominal dimensions from CAD model. Input uncertainty acceptable for MRL 2 decision."
    },
